FBIS4-37753 "drnes122cc_94002" FBIS-NES-94-122 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 Islamic Affairs New Islamist Group Active on Afghan-Pakistan Border New Islamist Group Active on Afghan-Pakistan Border NC2306184194 Cairo AL-WAFD in Arabic 15 Jun 94 p 6 NC2306184194 Cairo AL-WAFD Arabic BFN [From the "Political Week" section] [Text] A new Islamist organization calling itself the "Caliphate Group" has recently appeared. The organization, which espouses the concept of repudiation and accuses all existing Islamic societies and countries of apostasy, is operating in tribal territories adjacent to the Pakistani-Afghan border. It advocates the restoration of the caliphate under the leadership of the group's chief. The membership of the new organization comprises Egyptian, Sudanese, Jordanian, and Algerian nationals. The leader of the group is an Arab millionaire of Palestinian extraction called Abu-'Uthman. He considers himself an extension of Shukri Mustafa, leader of the Repudation and Renunciation group. Last week the Pakistani authorities asked the group's leading members to leave Pakistan.
